#: ../../source/reference/tensor/generated/maxframe.tensor.in1d.rst:2
msgid "maxframe.tensor.in1d"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:1 of
msgid ""
"Test whether each element of a 1-D tensor is also present in a second "
"tensor."
msgstr "测试一维张量中的每个元素是否也存在于第二个张量中。"

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:3 of
msgid ""
"Returns a boolean tensor the same length as `ar1` that is True where an "
"element of `ar1` is in `ar2` and False otherwise."
msgstr ""
"返回一个与 `ar1` 长度相同的布尔张量，当 `ar1` 中的元素在 `ar2` 中时为 "
"True，否则为 False。"

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:6 of
msgid "We recommend using :func:`isin` instead of `in1d` for new code."
msgstr "我们建议在新代码中使用 :func:`isin` 而不是 `in1d`。"

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d of
msgid "参数"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:8 of
msgid "Input tensor."
msgstr "输入张量。"

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:10 of
msgid "The values against which to test each value of `ar1`."
msgstr "用于测试 `ar1` 中每个值的参考值。"

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:12 of
msgid ""
"If True, the input tensors are both assumed to be unique, which can speed"
" up the calculation.  Default is False."
msgstr ""
"如果为 True，则假定输入张量中的元素都是唯一的，这可以加快计算速度。默认为"
" False。"

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:15 of
msgid ""
"If True, the values in the returned tensor are inverted (that is, False "
"where an element of `ar1` is in `ar2` and True otherwise). Default is "
"False. ``np.in1d(a, b, invert=True)`` is equivalent to (but is faster "
"than) ``np.invert(in1d(a, b))``."
msgstr ""
"如果为 True，则返回张量中的值会被反转（即 `ar1` 中存在于 `ar2` 的元素对应"
"为 False，否则为 True）。默认为 False。``np.in1d(a, b, invert=True)`` "
"等价于（但比）``np.invert(in1d(a, b))`` 更快。"

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d of
msgid "返回"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:21 of
msgid "**in1d** -- The values `ar1[in1d]` are in `ar2`."
msgstr "**in1d** -- `ar1[in1d]` 中的值存在于 `ar2` 中。"

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d of
msgid "返回类型"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:26 of
msgid ":py:obj:`isin`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:27 of
msgid "Version of this function that preserves the shape of ar1."
msgstr "保留 ar1 形状的该函数版本。"

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:29 of
msgid ":py:obj:`numpy.lib.arraysetops`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:30 of
msgid ""
"Module with a number of other functions for performing set operations on "
"arrays."
msgstr "包含多个用于对数组执行集合操作的函数的模块。"

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:33 of
msgid "备注"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.misc.in1d.in1d:34 of
msgid ""
"`in1d` can be considered as an element-wise function version of the "
"python keyword `in`, for 1-D sequences. ``in1d(a, b)`` is roughly "
"equivalent to ``mt.array([item in b for item in a])``. However, this idea"
" fails if `ar2` is a set, or similar (non-sequence) container:  As "
"``ar2`` is converted to a tensor, in those cases ``asarray(ar2)`` is an "
"object tensor rather than the expected tensor of contained values."
msgstr ""
"`in1d` 可以看作是 Python 关键字 `in` 在一维序列上的逐元素函数版本。``in1d"
"(a, b)`` 大致等价于 ``mt.array([item in b for item in a])``。但如果 `ar2`"
" 是集合或类似的（非序列）容器，这种想法就会失败：因为 ``ar2`` 会被转换为"
"张量，在这些情况下 ``asarray(ar2)`` 是一个对象张量，而不是预期的包含值的"
"张量。"

